{
  "name": "polish-the-video-editor-20260406-0351",
  "idea": "Polish the video-editor effect system to excellent quality. Three specific issues to fix: (1) Unify the wrapping code path \u2014 wrapWithClipEffects, EffectLayerSequence, and the preview's wrapPreviewEffect all independently construct effect component trees. Refactor so there's ONE canonical wrapping function that all three use. (2) Fix the effectFrames disagreement \u2014 wrapWithClipEffects omits effectFrames for continuous effects but EffectLayerSequence passes effectFrames=durationInFrames. Pick one contract and enforce it everywhere. (3) Clean up PREVIEW_FPS=30 \u2014 it's now only a fallback, replace with inline 30 and remove the constant. Also audit for: race conditions in async effect registration, inefficiencies in the render path (e.g. registry.getSchema called multiple times per frame), stale closures in makePreviewComposition, and any other code quality issues in the effect system files. Key files: effects/index.tsx, compositions/EffectLayerSequence.tsx, components/EffectCreatorPanel.tsx, effects/DynamicEffectRegistry.ts, hooks/useEffectRegistry.ts, effects/validateParams.ts, effects/EffectErrorBoundary.tsx",
